

                Angular- Front End Technology

                    BASIC COMMANDS

1. create a project - ng new project-name

2. to run Angular project- ng serve

3. to generate component - ng g c component - name

4. to create service - ng g s service-name


                    BASIC CONCEPTS

1. MODULE - to import libraries - root module -AppModule

2. Components - to generate ts,html,css,root component - AppComponent

3. Data Binding - sharing data within a component
   
    3.1 One way binding - only single direction sharing
       
        3.1.1 Component(ts file) to view(html)
            
            3.1.1.1 String Interpolation - {{variable-name}}
            
            3.1.1.2 Property Binding - [tag-attribute] = "class-property"
        
        3.1.2 View to Component
           
            3.1.2.1 Event Binding - (event-name)="function-call"
           
            3.1.2.2 Event Binding using $event - (event-name)="function-call"
           
            3.1.2.3 Template Referenncing variable: Syntax:- #variable-name
       
    3.2 Two way binding - same time data sharing in both directions
      
        3.2.1 FormsModule - Import in AppModule
                
                ngModel - Syntax : [(ngModel)]="variable-name" - set name attribute if it used inside from tag

4. Component Path set up,router-outlet selector

5. Dependency Injection - inside constructor of a class

6. Angular Service

7. ngSubmit

8. Angular forms
    
    8.1 Template Driven Form
    
    8.2 Model Driven Form - ReactiveForms - Import ReactiveFormsModule
    (form group , form array , form control)

9. Directives - DOM Manipulations
   
    9.1 Component Directives

    9.2 Structural Directives - prifixed with a symbol *

        9.2.1 *ngIf 

        9.2.1 *ngFor

    9.3 Attribute Directives - ngClass

10 . Parent Child communication

    10.1 Parent-Child - @Input()

    10.2 Child-Parent - @Output()